<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer6257285295062424998"><b>James M. McPherson</b>, Ph.D. (Johns Hopkins University, 1963; B.A., Gustavus Adolphus College (St. Peter, Minnesota), 1958) is an American Civil War historian, and the George Henry Davis &apos;86 Professor Emeritus of United States History at Princeton University. He received the Pulitzer Prize for <i>Battle Cry of Freedom</i>, his most famous book. He was the president of the American Historical Association in </span>
  <span id="freeText6257285295062424998" style="display:none"><b>James M. McPherson</b>, Ph.D. (Johns Hopkins University, 1963; B.A., Gustavus Adolphus College (St. Peter, Minnesota), 1958) is an American Civil War historian, and the George Henry Davis '86 Professor Emeritus of United States History at Princeton University. He received the Pulitzer Prize for <i>Battle Cry of Freedom</i>, his most famous book. He was the president of the American Historical Association in 2003, and is a member of the editorial board of Encyclopædia Britannica.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6257285295062424998" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

